    "analysis": "The previous step computed global per-(cmdb_id, kpi_name) aggregates (count, p95, mean, max) over the full available metric series. Example top rows show many service KPIs (e.g., carts cpu/mem/latency/socket), and there are ~25 samples per series in metric.csv. These global p95 thresholds are now available to use for anomaly detection. Next, we must apply those global thresholds to the metric samples that fall inside the incident window (2024-01-20 16:25:45 to 2024-01-20 16:55:45 UTC) to find KPIs that exceed their global p95 during the incident (candidate faults). We should keep outputs compact (per-series aggregates) to narrow candidates before inspecting traces/logs.",
